1 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution of
2 the State of Iowa is proposed:
3 Article I of the Constitution of the State of Iowa is amended
4 by adding the following new section:
5 Sec. 10A. Protection of children and other witnesses. To
6 protect children under the age of eighteen and any witness
7 with a mental illness, intellectual disability, or other
8 developmental disability, the right of an accused to confront
9 such witnesses may be limited by law.
10 Sec. 2. REFERRAL AND PUBLICATION. The foregoing proposed
11 amendment to the Constitution of the State of Iowa is referred
12 to the general assembly to be chosen at the next general
13 election for members of the general assembly, and shall be
14 published as provided by law for three months previous to the
15 date of that election.
16 EXPLANATION
17 The inclusion of this explanation does not constitute agreement with
