19 This joint resolution proposes an amendment to the
20 Constitution of the State of Iowa relating to the right of an
21 accused to confront children and other witnesses.
22 The resolution provides that in order to protect children
23 under the age of 18 and any witness with a mental illness,
24 intellectual disability, or other developmental disability, the
25 right of an accused to confront such witnesses may be limited
26 by law.
27 The resolution, if adopted, would be published and then
28 referred to the next general assembly (92nd) for adoption,
29 before being submitted to the electorate for ratification.
